  "instructions": [
    "Rinse mung beans and soak in 3 cups water overnight for fermentation.",
    "Heat oil in a pan, add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, fenugreek seeds, dried red chilies, and curry leaves until mustard seeds splutter.",
    "Add diced tomato and sauté until soft.",
    "Stir in tamarind paste, salt, and jaggery, then pour in the soaked mung beans with their soaking water.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 30 minutes until beans are chewy.",
    "Skim off any foam that rises to the top during simmering.",
    "Taste and adjust salt or tamarind if needed.",
    "Serve hot over rice or with roti, garnished with fresh coriander if desired."
